The paper deals with coding theory and distributed storage systems, which are topics that fall under information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the tradeoff between reliability and efficiency, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC) and systems and control (cs.SI). Finally, the paper proposes a family of topologies for codes, which involves optimization and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
